{"title_page": "2018 England rugby union tour of South Africa", "text_new": "{{Infobox Tour Rugby\n|tour = 2018 England rugby union tour of South Africa\n|coach = [[Eddie Jones (rugby union)|Eddie Jones]]\n|captain = [[Owen Farrell]]\n|top test point scorer = \n|top test try scorer = \n|matchplayed = 3\n|matchwon = 1\n|matchdraw = 0\n|matchlost = 2\n|testplayed = 3\n|testwon = 1\n|testdraw = 0\n|testlost = 2\n|opponent1 = {{ru|South Africa}}\n|icon1 =\n|played1 = 3\n|won1 = 1\n|draw1 = 0\n|lost1 = 2\n|previous = [[2017 England rugby union tour of Argentina|Argentina 2017]]\n|next = TBA\n}}\n\nIn June 2018, [[England national rugby union team|England]] played a three-test series against {{nrut|South Africa}} as part of the [[2018 mid-year rugby union internationals|2018 mid-year rugby union tests]]. The series was part of the sixth year of the global rugby calendar established by [[World Rugby]], which runs through to 2019.<ref>{{cite news|title=IRB approve new 10-year playing schedule|url=http://www.rugbyweek.com/25946-irb-approve-new-10-year-playing-schedule/|accessdate=20 June 2016|work=Rugby Week|date=18 May 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Fixtures==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:0px\"| Date and time\n! style=\"width:0px\"| Venue\n! style=\"width:118px\"| Home\n! style=\"width:70px\"| Score\n! style=\"width:118px\"| Away\n|-\n| 9 June 2018\n| [[Ellis Park Stadium|Ellis Park]], [[Johannesburg]]\n| {{ru-rt|South Africa}}\n| '''42\u201339'''\n| {{ru|England}}\n|-\n| 16 June 2018\n| [[Free State Stadium]], [[Bloemfontein]]\n| {{ru-rt|South Africa}}\n| '''23\u201312'''\n| {{ru|England}}\n|-\n| 23 June 2018\n| [[Newlands Stadium|Newlands]], [[Cape Town]]\n| {{ru-rt|South Africa}}\n| '''10\u201325'''\n| {{ru|England}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Squads==\n<small>'''Note:''' Ages, caps and clubs are as per 9 June, the first test match of the tour.</small>\n\n===England===\nOn 29 May, England finalised a 34-man tour squad for their 3-test series summer tour of [[South Africa national rugby union team|South Africa]].<ref>[http://www.englandrugby.com/news/england-squad-for-south-africa-finalised/ England squad for South Africa finalised]</ref>\n\nOn 11 June, Jack Singleton joined the squad as a third choice hooker option and injury cover for Luke Cowan-Dickie.<ref>[http://www.englandrugby.com/news/south-africa-england-jack-singleton-second-test/ Singleton added to England squad]</ref>\n\n'''Coaching team:'''\n* '''Head coach:''' {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Eddie Jones (rugby union)|Eddie Jones]]\n* '''Attack coach:''' {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Scott Wisemantel]]\n* '''Defence coach:''' {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Paul Gustard]]\n* '''Forwards coach:''' {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Steve Borthwick]]\n* '''Scrum coach:''' {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Neal Hatley]]\n{{nat rs start|hidenote=yes}}\n{{nat rs player|pos=HK|name={{sortname|Luke|Cowan-Dickie}}|age={{Birth date and age2|2018|6|9|1993|6|20|df=y}}|caps=7|club=[[Exeter Chiefs]]|clubnat=ENG}}\n{{nat rs player|pos=HK|name={{sortname|Jamie|George}}|age={{Birth date and age2|2018|6|9|1990|10|20|df=y}}|caps=25|club=[[Saracens F.C.|Saracens]]|clubnat=ENG}}\n{{nat rs player|pos=HK|name={{sortname|Jack|Singleton}}|age={{Birth date and age2|2018|6|9|1996|5|14|df=y}}|caps=0|club=[[Worcester Warriors]]|clubnat=ENG}}\n{{nat rs player|pos=PR|name={{sortname|Ellis|Genge}}|age={{Birth date and age2|2018|6|9|1995|2|16|df=y}}|caps=5|club=[[Leicester Tigers]]|clubnat=ENG}}\n{{nat rs player|pos=PR|name={{sortname|Joe|Marler}}|age={{Birth date and age2|2018|6|9|1990|7|7|df=y}}|caps=56|club=[[Harlequin F.C.|Harlequins]]|clubnat=ENG}}\n{{nat rs player|pos=PR|name={{sortname|Kyle|Sinckler}}|age={{Birth date and age2|2018|6|9|1992|3|30|df=y}}|caps=10|club=[[Harlequin F.C.|Harlequins]]|clubnat=ENG}}\n{{nat rs player|pos=PR|name={{sortname|Mako|Vunipola}}|age={{Birth date and age2|2018|6|9|1991|1|14|df=y}}|caps=49|club=[[Saracens F.C.|Saracens]]|clubnat=ENG}}\n{{nat rs player|pos=PR|name={{sortname|Harry|Williams|dab=rugby union}}|age=